node.text:
Visit @SculptMovements 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit! .
Treino de MMI com 01. Agachamento máquina 15/12/10 + drop com extensora 4 x 4 / 4x3 / 4x2 /4x 1 aumentando a carga ( 1 série ) 
1 x 10 com pico de contração em cima + 10 saindo da inércia 
1 x 10 com excêntrica lenta + 10 concêntrica lenta + 10 
02. Stiff 3 x 15 + bom dia 10 
03. Flexora 9 x 6 alternando a carga entre leva e pesado 
1 x 30 curtas + 10 isometria + 12 
1 x unilateral 8 /7/6 até zerar sem intervalo 
04. Flexora em pé 3 x 12 parando no meio + glúteo no cabo 3 x 12 
Panturrilhas sempre 😅
Macacão @santtaloren
.
.
.
Credit @graoficial #Fitness #fitfam #fitspo #motivation #workout #workoutvideo #legday #gym #abs

node.text:
Save & visit @EatsConnoisseur for daily delicious foods & recipes to get you slim🥝🍓🍌🍇 

 Which one(s)🍞🥚🍳🥑 are your most favorite: 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5?
All by @toastedtable 😋
.
1. Smashed avocado on whole grain toast, hard boiled eggs, aleppo pepper, sesame seeds & honey🥑
.
2. Then I made this (with lots of TJs ingredients): traderjoes whole grain Ekeziel bread topped with avocado smashed with za’atar & a soft-boiled egg🥑
.
3. Back home for break 🤗 with this little toast: balthazarbakery’s multigrain sourdough, smashed avo, soft-boiled eggs, honey, aleppo pepper & caraway seeds 🥑
.
4. On my toast: smashed avocado, soft-boiled eggs, tahini, chili flakes & honey on traderjoes whole grain sourdough 🥑🥑
.
5. Morning toast: Smashed avocado with baked spicy salmon (yes I put cooked salmon on my toast, yes it was cold, yes it tasted delicious) & a poached egg with dill & chili flakes🔥
.
Enjoy and Have a great day!🥑🌸
.
#avocado #tasty #toast #yummy #healthy #healthyfood #healthyrecipes

node.text:
sculptlifestyletrain ABS ON FIRE 🔥 [save, share, and tag your friends ] you’re going to love this one (read below). Save & @SculptMobility for daily pain management, flexibility, and workout advice📚 

Workout details: perform 3-4 sets of 8-10 slow repetitions per movement. You can perform all sets of one movement, or do master circuit performing one set of each with 30s rest.

Note: Core exercises help strengthen your abdominal wall but exercises alone without a balanced and consistent nutrition plan, won’t help you decrease body fat to reveal the muscle you’ve built overtime.

Strength training with coumpound movements will actually be more beneficial to build overall strength and muscle; that is in  combination with a balanced nutrition that is geared towards muscle building. All macronutrients (especially carbs and protein) are extremely important in order to put on muscle mass and recover the muscle that is torn during exercise. 

The one goal in mind when trying to lose body fat is that you’ll need “spend” some good amount of energy (burn calories). Combining strength training with moderate cardio (depending on your goals) is a great strategy when thinking of better body composition.

Strat writing down your routines including what you eat. You can only get better and understand your nutritional needs when you have a plan to execute on a cosistent basis.
Credit @massy.arias #Fitness #fitfam #fitspo #motivation #workout #workoutvideo #legday #gym #abs

node.text:
No mistake. 😶 Last #cleanandjerk warm-up by 8-year-old weightlifter and gymnast @roryvanulft, before defending her title at the USA Weightlifting Youth National Championships. This rep? American record + 6 kg.

Credit @roryvanulft

This workout almost snatched my soul away the other day, so naturally I wanted to share it with you all 💀😭

LIKE♥️ + SAVE💾 to try this later!

Broken into 3 supersets 
Superset 1: 
Elevated goblet squat 4 x 10
Elevated goblet squat pulses 4 x 20
 
Superset 2:
Forward DB lunges 4 x 8 each leg
Leg extension triple drop set x 4 sets

Superset 3:
RDLs 4 x 12
Seated hamstring curl triple drop set x 4 sets

No need to do the drop sets if you can’t l, just go straight into 4 x 10 reps if it’s too much cus they actually kill idk why I did that🤧🥵

Anyways, yeah, Happy Saturday 🥳

credit @mildred523_  #Fitness #fitfam #fitspo #motivation #workout #workoutvideo #legday #gym #abs

node.text:
What is your favorite “leg-killer”? 🦵🏼🔥 Visit @GymGlutes 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit!

 I put a fast finisher here in hot Greece that definitely burned! 😅

 🔹 Cossack Shoulder press 3-4 / side
 🔹 Goblet squat + reverse lung 3-4x
 🔹 SA OH walking lungs 5x side & arm

 👉🏼4 rounds!

 After a long time working on the secret project on the subject of the intestine (you probably still don't know what the project will be😅) I'm off to dinner with my dad who came to visit us for the first time

 I wish you a great evening! ❤️

 Music: @epidemicsound
Credit @mariesteff #Fitness #fitfam #fitspo #motivation #workout #workoutvideo #legday #gym #abs

node.text:
I’ve gained and lost weight throughout Covid. I know this not because I weigh myself — I don’t, I refuse to — but because I can see it in my body, feel it in my skin.

And that’s ok.

There’s was a time when these kind of changes would have sent me into a tailspin.

I viewed my WEIGHT as intrinsically tied to my WORTH.
And changes in it were measures of GOOD or BAD.
SUCCESS or FAILURE.

Today, now, I don’t play that game.
I don’t even let myself go there.

Instead, when I find my mind sliding into that dangerous space,
Of staring down flaws in the mirror or searching out fistfuls of squishy skin with my hands,
I pull back. I pause.
And I ask myself what is really bothering me.

Sometimes, yes, sometimes it’s my body.
Because that’s human and that’s conditioned.
But more often than that, it’s emotional.
Mental.
Maybe a lack of control in this or feeling not good enough in that.

And whatever the answer is,
I treat it gently.

Because self love isn’t about feeling shiny in your skin every single moment.
It’s knowing that who you ARE doesn’t CHANGE even if your body does.

So today, today I just wanted to remind you these things.
Especially now, as my inbox is full with so many messages on Covid and body image struggles.

I just wanted to stress how incredible you are.
How powerful. How strong.
And how even if your WEIGHT fluctuates,
Your WORTH does not.

I’m so glad you’re here.
I’m grateful we’re in this together.️⁣⁣️️️️️️️️️️️️

node.text:
Ladies you NEED to check out @SculptSwim for summers hottest bikinis 👙 

Do you want to get toned? Build lean muscle? ⁣
⁣
Well you’re going about it the wrong way⁣
⁣
These things will NOT get you toned:⁣
⁣
❌ lifting light weights⁣
⁣
❌ doing random exercises every week⁣
⁣
❌ doing a ton of cardio (you can actually burn off your muscle)⁣
⁣
❌ doing high reps and going for burn out⁣
⁣
INSTEAD try this⁣
⁣
✅ stick to structured workouts for 4 weeks minimum before changing them up⁣
⁣
…. Yes it sometimes gets boring⁣
⁣
✅ lift as heavy as you can with proper form and focus on trying to lift heavier each week⁣
⁣
…. No you won’t get bulky I promise⁣
⁣
✅ rep ranges 6-12 is for muscle hypertrophy (muscle growth)⁣
⁣
…… Reps 1-5 are for maximal strength and 12-20+ for muscle endurance (NASM)⁣
⁣
✅ eat adequate protein⁣
⁣
…….. aim for .8-1.1g per lb of lean body mass⁣
⁣
⁣
But most importantly BE PATIENT⁣
⁣
Building muscle and getting toned take time and consistency⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
